        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-22T16:46:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we will want to differentiate Host temperature and device temperature",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 52,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 52,
        "endChar": 12
      },
      "revId": "17d7fc07141df4765aae91e2c8f8b42537a17a7a",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0b449664_7f048a7f",
        "filename": "machine/go/machine/machine.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 52,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-22T16:46:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I am skeptical about condensing temperature down to a single value. I worry that this will lead to frustrations like \"Why is this device too hot?\" because all we have is a single number. \n\nI would probably go with a map of sensor_name -\u003e float32\n\nIn any case, it should be more clear if this is the maximum temperature, the average temperature, or something else.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 52,
        "startChar": 13,
        "endLine": 52,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "17d7fc07141df4765aae91e2c8f8b42537a17a7a",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
