    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9543f603_4c5c38f5",
        "filename": "machine/go/machine/processor/impl.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 288,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-22T16:46:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do we know how well this supports older devices? FWIW, swarming just reads /sys/class/thermal directly\nhttps://github.com/luci/luci-py/blob/e0a8a5640c4104e5c90781d833168aa8a8d1f24d/appengine/third_party/python-adb/adb/contrib/high.py#L626",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 288,
        "startChar": 20,
        "endLine": 288,
        "endChar": 52
      },
      "revId": "17d7fc07141df4765aae91e2c8f8b42537a17a7a",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "87b6c7fb_0f63540d",
        "filename": "machine/go/machine/processor/impl.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 288,
      "author": {
        "id": 5205
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-22T19:43:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "AFAIK that requires root, and you are looking at raw device values as opposed to a higher level output from the service. If a device doesn\u0027t support thermalservice I\u0027d rather fall back to just battery temp.",
      "parentUuid": "9543f603_4c5c38f5",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 288,
        "startChar": 20,
        "endLine": 288,
        "endChar": 52
      },
      "revId": "17d7fc07141df4765aae91e2c8f8b42537a17a7a",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b5288d2a_566248ec",
        "filename": "machine/go/machine/processor/impl.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 312,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-22T16:46:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We will probably need a way to conditionally ignore certain sensors - we\u0027ve discovered several that have a fixed temperature.\nhttps://chrome-internal.googlesource.com/infradata/config/+/refs/heads/master/configs/chromium-swarm/scripts/skia_mobile.py#717",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 312,
        "startChar": 47,
        "endLine": 312,
        "endChar": 56
      },
      "revId": "17d7fc07141df4765aae91e2c8f8b42537a17a7a",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e18bd585_29708ad5",
        "filename": "machine/go/machine/processor/impl.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 312,
      "author": {
        "id": 5205
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-22T19:43:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I am going to presume that comes from mucking around in /sys/class/thermal directly. We can fix later if this shows up in thermalservice.",
      "parentUuid": "b5288d2a_566248ec",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 312,
        "startChar": 47,
        "endLine": 312,
        "endChar": 56
      },
      "revId": "17d7fc07141df4765aae91e2c8f8b42537a17a7a",
